Here someone is just repairing my kitchen floor. And I'm pretending right now that I still have a job and am working from home while sitting through Too Hot to Handle.
If only I could damn well manage to open the file. (Fucking One Drive.)
*Hacker voice* I'm in.
And that's when he starts drilling super loudly. Great.
It feels uncomfortably passive-aggressive to turn up my air purifier all the way, but I can smell the wood dust, so it would even be okay if he wasn't a mask opponent. Do I really need to protect myself?
I really would like to go back to bed, but I can't do that before he leaves.
At least I finally finished Chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but so damned terrifying. Oh yes, that's the good stuff!
I'm doing search and replace for … ➡️ Ellipsis symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But no, I'll stick with it. Natural language is usually fragmented, especially when one becomes emotional.
The handyman is now using the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully, that means he'll be done soon.
He went out to cut something (it sounds like it). I sneaked a peek to see how far he had gotten. There's still a lot left to do :(.
7 more pages in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter and it's quite neat – mainly changes to the text and very small corrections to direct speech, and I need to make everything a bit more concise. But I really could use a break and some tea right now, but the guy is still in my kitchen.
Now he's started vacuuming again. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The kitchen guy is gone!
He told me that he had made a cost estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were too tight and only paid for the part next to the door that isn't in good condition anymore. That feels much better.
The house is being ventilated, and my air purifier is running in the kitchen while I drink tea in the garden!
